<<.from-version "5.3.6">> The [[web server configuration parameter|WebServer Parameters]] ''http2'' determines whether the server uses the HTTP/2 protocol when TLS certificates are available.

When set to "yes" (the default), the server will use HTTP/2 with automatic HTTP/1.1 fallback support. When set to "no", the server will use HTTPS with HTTP/1.1 only.

HTTP/2 provides significant performance improvements for lazy-loading scenarios where many tiddlers are loaded in parallel. The multiplexing feature of HTTP/2 allows all requests to be processed simultaneously over a single connection, eliminating the head-of-line blocking issues of HTTP/1.1.

!! Requirements

* HTTP/2 requires TLS certificates to be configured via [[tls-cert|WebServer Parameter: tls-cert]] and [[tls-key|WebServer Parameter: tls-key]]
* Node.js 8.4.0 or later (the `http2` module is built-in)
* If certificates are not configured, HTTP/2 will be disabled regardless of this setting

!! Default Value

```
yes
```

!! Examples

Enable HTTP/2 (default behavior when certificates are configured):

```
tiddlywiki mywiki --listen tls-key=key.pem tls-cert=server.crt http2=yes
```

Disable HTTP/2 and use HTTP/1.1 over TLS:

```
tiddlywiki mywiki --listen tls-key=key.pem tls-cert=server.crt http2=no
```

